## evaluation
Continuous Ranked Probability Score (CRPS) is derived based on the predicted scalar value.
The CRPS is computed as follows:
$$
C=\frac{1}{199N}\sum_{m=1}^N\sum_{n=-99}^{99}(P(y\geq n)-H(n-Y_m))^2
$$
$H(x)=1$ if $x\geq 0$ else $0$
